HEADWORD: Hedonic
<hw>He*don"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/
pleasure, <?/ sweet, pleasant.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to
pleasure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or relating to Hedonism or the Hedonic
sect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hedonic sect</b></col> <cd>a sect that placed the highest
good in the gratification of the senses, -- called also
<altname>Cyrenaic sect</altname>, (which see), and <altname>School of
Aristippus</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hedonics</ent>⟦br⟧
